			<item>
				<title>Notes on Problems of Functional Analysis</title>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;This file records discussions on some problems in functional analysis&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;let-u-x-times-x-rightarrow-c-be-a-semi-inner-product-defined-on-x-and-let-mathscrxxuxx0-x-in-x-prove-that-mathscrx-is-a-linear-space&quot;&gt;1 Let &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u: X \times X \rightarrow C&lt;/script&gt; be a semi-inner product defined on &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;X&lt;/script&gt;, and let &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\mathscr{X}=\{x|u(x,x)=0, x \in X\}&lt;/script&gt;, prove that &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\mathscr{X}&lt;/script&gt; is a linear space&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;this problem shows the power of CBS inequality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) For any &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;x\in\mathscr{X}&lt;/script&gt;, any &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\alpha \in C&lt;/script&gt;, we have &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(\alpha x, \alpha x) = \alpha\bar\alpha u(x,x) = 0&lt;/script&gt;, so &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\alpha x \in \mathscr{X}&lt;/script&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) For any &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;x,y\in\mathscr{X}&lt;/script&gt;, because &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(\cdot,\cdot)&lt;/script&gt; is an semi-inner product, we have &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(x,y)u(y,x)\ge0&lt;/script&gt;. On the other hand, by CBS inequality, we have &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(x,y)u(y,x)\le u(x,x)u(y,y)=0&lt;/script&gt;. So &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(x,y)u(y,x)=0&lt;/script&gt;. Then &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(x,y)=u(y,x)=0&lt;/script&gt; (&amp;#8211;&amp;gt; This is itself a very interesting result). So &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u(x+y,x+y) = u(x,x) + u(x,y) + u(y,x) + u(y,y) = 0&lt;/script&gt;, then &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;x+y \in \mathscr{X}&lt;/script&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 15 Oct 2013 00:00:00 +1100</pubDate>
				<link>http://yuhonglin.github.io/2013/10/15/notes-on-problems-of-functional-analysis.html</link>
				<guid isPermaLink="true">http://yuhonglin.github.io/2013/10/15/notes-on-problems-of-functional-analysis.html</guid>
