			<item>
				<title>Matlab R2012a GCC Setting in Ubuntu</title>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;This file describes how to configure Matlab to compile c/c++ code in Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h2 id=&quot;let-mcc-use-gcc-44&quot;&gt;Let mcc use gcc-4.4&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The version of gcc that Matlab R2012a works with is &amp;#8220;4.4&amp;#8221; which is lower than the default version in Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.1 Install &lt;code&gt;gcc-4.4&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;gfortran-4.4&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bash&quot;&gt; 
   sudo apt-get install gcc-4.4 gfortran-4.4
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.2 Set mcc to use the lower version of &lt;code&gt;gcc&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;gfortran&lt;/code&gt;: Edit file &lt;code&gt;~/.matlab/R2012a/mexopts.sh&lt;/code&gt; (need root), replace &lt;code&gt;gcc&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;gcc-4.4&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;g++&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;g++-4.4&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;gfortran&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;gfortran-4.4&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h2 id=&quot;let-matlab-use-the-dynamic-library-of-os&quot;&gt;Let MATLAB use the dynamic library of OS&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;After step 1, there may be errors still in linking step. The simplest way of solving this is to rename (or remove) the dynamic libraries used in folder &lt;code&gt;~/MATLAB/R2012a/sys/os/glnxa64/&lt;/code&gt;, for example,&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;   &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~/MATLAB/R2012a/sys/os/glnxa64/
   mv libXm.so.3 ./libXm.so.3.backup
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do this for all the &lt;code&gt;.so&lt;/code&gt; files that meet error.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 05 Oct 2013 00:00:00 +1000</pubDate>
				<link>http://yuhonglin.github.io/2013/10/05/MATLAB2012a-gcc-setting-on-ubuntu.html</link>
				<guid isPermaLink="true">http://yuhonglin.github.io/2013/10/05/MATLAB2012a-gcc-setting-on-ubuntu.html</guid>
			</item>
		
